commit.message: CI: test with GAP 4.13; test with mininimal set of packages loaded
Fix test: don't implicitly rely on AsList returning a sorted list
Don't abuse InfoWarning for an additional banner
rm extra hyphen, mention Gap.app as xgap alternate
Update GPL links to use https

Fix placement of HTML manual

For packages with multiple help books *and* using the old-style gapmacro
documentation system, GAP expects the HTML files to be in `doc/htm/BOOK`,
not `htm/BOOK`.

Overhaul docs generation

- actually generate bibliography in HTML and PDF
- actually generate index in PDF
- add missing manual.mst files, for index generation
- ensure `doc/make_doc` exits with an error if any step fails, instead
  of just plodding on, and burying error messages between tons of TeX
  output
- don't bundle convert.pl, use GAP's
- remove old `htm` directory, so we don't carry around outdated files
- put the index into a single page
- use Unicode for math

CI: Ensure code coverage reporting will work in February 2022 and beyond

See https://github.com/gap-actions/process-coverage/issues/10
tst/testall.g: test up to whitespace only
Migrate from Travis to GitHub Actions

Merge pull request #15 from gap-packages/mh/license

PackageInfo.g: add License field ; Rename gpl-2.0.txt -> LICENSE

commit.message:
Update Travis integration

Update Travis integration to use scripts from a central repository. This
allows us to apply fixes and improvements to these scripts for all
packages, and also removes some clutter from package repositories.
